This article is about the children's book by Karen Hesse, and not the book by Patricia Schonstein. A Time of Angels is a book by the Newberry medalist Karen Hesse and follows the life of a young Jewish girl, Hannah, during the influenza pandemic of 1918-1919. Hannah lives in New York, but when her sisters come down with influenza, she's forced to go to the country. She herself becomes very sick with influenza, but an elderly German man takes her in, and nurses her back to health.
